cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.Distributed, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with distributed online prediction algorithms, which are typically studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with distributed optimization, which falls under the purview of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper explicitly takes into account communication latencies between nodes, which is a key aspect of distributed computing, further supporting these categories. Additionally, the paper deals with online prediction, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely category as well.
